{{no footnotes|date=March 2013}}
{{notable|date=March 2013}}
The '''Human Race Machine''' (HRM) is a [[computer graphics|computerized]] [[System console|console]] composed of four different programs. The Human Race Machine program allows participants to see themselves with the facial characteristics of six different [[racial group|races]]: [[Asian people|Asian]], [[White people|White]], [[Ethnic groups of Africa|African]], [[Middle Eastern]], and [[India]]n, mapped onto their own face.  The Age Machine allows viewers see an aged version of his or her face. A version of this methodology has been used for over twenty years by the [[FBI]] and the [[National Center for Missing and Exploited Children]] to help locate kidnap victims and missing children. The Couples Machine combines photographs of two people in different percentages to show the appearance of their child. The Anomaly Machine lets viewers see themselves with facial anomalies. The HRM was created by [[artist]] [[Nancy Burson]] and David Kramlich; it uses [[morphing]] technology.  It was shown on [[The Oprah Winfrey Show|Oprah]] on 2006-02-16.

